			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">ODP</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">ODP</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Emissions</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other substance type</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Ozone Depletion Potential (ODP) is a measure of the amount of ozone depletion caused by a substance. It is used to regulate ozone-depleting substances (ODS), which are classified as either Class I or Class II. Class I substances, such as chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs) and halons, have a higher ODP and have been phased out in the U.S. Class II substances, such as hydrochlorofluorocarbons (HCFCs), have a lower ODP. Ozone layer depletion increases the amount of harmful UVB radiation that reaches the Earth's surface, which can cause skin cancer and cataracts.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">臭氧消耗潜能值是衡量物质造成的臭氧消耗量的指标。它用于调节被归类为I类或II类的消耗臭氧层物质。I类物质，如氯氟烃和哈龙，具有较高的臭氧消耗潜能值，并已在美国逐步淘汰，II类物质，如氢氯氟烃具有较低的臭氧消耗潜能值。臭氧层消耗会增加到达地球表面的有害UVB辐射量，从而导致皮肤癌和白内障。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
